al":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"In regular intervals users open issues because they are struggling AWS Lambda. Lambda requires a specific type of binary extensions that works on X86_64 platforms with old glib. Recent versions of pip have a way to download and unpack the correct files into a target directory. I propose to include a FAQ entry\r\n\r\n## optionally: create virtual env and install latest pip\r\n```\r\n$ python3 -m venv venv\r\n$ venv/bin/pip install -U pip setuptools\r\n$ . venv/bin/activate\r\n```\r\n\r\n## download cryptography and dependencies\r\n\r\n```\r\n$ pip install \\\r\n    --platform manylinux2010_x86_64 \\\r\n    --implementation cp \\\r\n    --python 3.9 \\\r\n    --only-binary=:all: --upgrade \\\r\n    --target awsbundle \\\r\n    cryptography\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis will download and unpack cryptography and all its dependencies for Python 3.9 into the ``awsbundle`` directory:\r\n\r\n```\r\n$ ls awsbundle/\r\ncffi\r\ncffi-1.14.6.dist-info\r\n_cffi_backend.cpython-36m-x86_64-linux-gnu.so\r\ncffi.libs\r\ncryptography\r\ncryptography-35.0.0.dist-info\r\npycparser\r\npycparser-2.20.dist-info\r\n$ find awsbundle/ -name '*.so' \r\nawsbundle/_cffi_backend.cpython-36m-x86_64-linux-gnu.so\r\nawsbundle/cryptography/hazmat/bindings/_openssl.abi3.so\r\nawsbundle/cryptography/hazmat/bindings/_rust.abi3.so\r\n```","closed_by":{"login":"reaperhulk","id":161495,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE2MTQ5NQ==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/161495?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/reaperhulk","html_url":"https://github.com/reaperhulk","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/reaperhulk/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/reaperhulk/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/reaperhulk/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/reaperhulk/starred{/own